**Title:** REG - Scholarships - SAINTCON

**Overview:** The UtahSAINT Organization has established a Conference Scholarship Program to support talented and promising "hackers" in attending the SAINTCON event. For SAINTCON 2023, up to 20 scholarships will be offered.

**Eligibility Criteria:**
- Applicants must be at least 14 years old.
- Applicants under 18 must be accompanied by an adult attendee not dependent on a scholarship.
- Applicants must not be employed by a company that pays for attendance.
- An essay submission is required.

**Scholarship Inclusions:**
- Free pass to the conference, including lunches and snacks.

**Exclusions:**
- Does not cover travel, hotel, additional meals, and other expenses.

**Application Process:**
- Submissions are reviewed by a panel of security professionals.
- Notifications of awards are sent to the email provided in the application.
- Scholarship awards must be registered within seven days of notification.
- Tickets are non-transferable and must be used by the awarded applicant.

**Contact for Further Clarification:**
- Interested individuals are encouraged to reach out for discussions on group scholarships.

**Links:**
- Submit Scholarship Application: [Application Form](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSclkFFJVvNX79viVlEE1hSbbuAb5VtIssRn4POV2bEhDV89Sw/viewform)
- More Information on SAINTCON: [SAINTCON Official Site](https://saintcon.org)